<section xml:id="bns_provserv_nova" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:raxm="http://docs.rackspace.com/api/metadata" version="5.0">
    <title>Various Shared Provision Server Text</title>
    <!-- notes common to neutron and nova & client and curl -->
    <para xml:id="bns_ps_notes">
        <note>
            <para>You cannot attach an isolated network to an existing server. However, to work around this limitation, you
                can create an image of the server and build a new server based on that image. When you build the new server,
                you can attach the isolated network. For information, see
                <link xlink:href="http://www.rackspace.com/knowledge_center/article/attach-an-existing-cloud-server-to-a-cloud-network">
                <citetitle>Attach a Cloud Network to an Existing Cloud Server</citetitle></link>.
                To use the create image API, see
                <link xlink:href="http://docs.rackspace.com/servers/api/v2/cs-devguide/content/Create_Image-d1e4655.html">
                Create Image</link>.</para>
        </note>
        <note>
            <para>You can use the &virt_ext; to attach an isolated network to an existing server. For information, see <olink
                    targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted" targetptr="attach_net">Attach Your Network to an Existing
                Server</olink>.</para>
        </note>
    </para>

    <!-- neutron paramaters for call, client and curl -->
    <epigraph xml:id="bns_ps_params_neutron">
        <para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The name of the new server. Use a name of your choice.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The image ID. For how to list images, see
                        <link xlink:href="http://docs.rackspace.com/servers/api/v2/cs-gettingstarted/content/list_images.html">
                    List Images</link>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The flavor ID. For how to list flavors, see
                        <link xlink:href="http://docs.rackspace.com/servers/api/v2/cs-gettingstarted/content/list_flavors.html">
                    List Flavors</link>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The port ID of your isolated network. This is the ID you copied in either <olink
                            targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted" targetptr="neutron_create_port_neutron">“Create a port (neutron
                            API/neutron)”</olink> or <olink targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted"
                            targetptr="neutron_create_port_curl">“Create a port (neutron API/cURL)”</olink></para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
        <para>You specify these values as parameters in a nova command.</para>
    </epigraph>

    <!-- nova paramaters for call, client and curl -->
    <epigraph xml:id="bns_ps_params_nova">
        <para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The name of the new server. Use a name of your choice.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The image ID. For how to list images, see
                        <link xlink:href="http://docs.rackspace.com/servers/api/v2/cs-gettingstarted/content/list_images.html">
                    List Images</link>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The flavor ID. For how to list flavors, see
                        <link xlink:href="http://docs.rackspace.com/servers/api/v2/cs-gettingstarted/content/list_flavors.html">
                    List Flavors</link>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The network ID of your isolated network. This is the ID you copied in either <olink
                            targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted" targetptr="nova_create_network_nova">“Create a network
                            (nova-network API/nova)”</olink> or <olink targetdoc="cn-gettingstarted"
                            targetptr="nova_create_network_curl">“Create a network (nova-network API/cURL)”</olink></para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
        <para>You specify these values as parameters in a cURL command.</para>
    </epigraph>

